Roper Technologies, Inc. (ROP) Position Lowered by Nuveen Asset Management LLC


					Posted by Chloe McGuire on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments




Nuveen Asset Management LLC cut its stake in shares of  Roper Technologies, Inc. (NYSE:ROP) by 73.0% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor  owned 6,403 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 17,296 shares during the period. Nuveen Asset Management LLC’s holdings in Roper Technologies were worth $1,322,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other large investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the stock. Quadrature Capital Ltd purchased a new stake in shares of  Roper Technologies during the fourth quarter valued at $4,950,000.  Teachers Advisors LLC increased its position in  Roper Technologies by 50.8% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 342,533 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $62,711,000 after buying an additional 115,326 shares in the last quarter.  Kentucky Retirement Systems bought a new position in  Roper Technologies during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $1,347,000.  Kentucky Retirement Systems Insurance Trust Fund bought a new position in  Roper Technologies during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $601,000.  Finally, Highbridge Capital Management LLC bought a new position in  Roper Technologies during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $1,227,000. 96.71% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 


 Get Roper Technologies Inc. alerts:



Roper Technologies, Inc. (ROP) opened at 236.06 on Thursday. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $232.09 and its 200 day moving average is $213.13. The company has a market capitalization of $24.09 billion, a PE ratio of 36.43 and a beta of 1.05. Roper Technologies, Inc. has a one year low of $159.28 and a one year high of $238.49. 





Roper Technologies (NYSE:ROP) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Friday, April 28th. The industrial products company reported $2.11 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $1.99 by $0.12. The company had revenue of $1.09 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.09 billion. Roper Technologies had a net margin of 16.74% and a return on equity of 12.81%. The business’s revenue for the quarter was up 20.4% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the prior year, the firm earned $1.81 earnings per share.  On average, equities analysts expect that  Roper Technologies, Inc. will post $9.21 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, July 21st. Shareholders of record on Friday, July 7th will be paid a dividend of $0.35 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, July 5th. This represents a $1.40 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 0.59%. Roper Technologies’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 21.60%. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Roper Technologies, Inc. (ROP) Position Lowered by Nuveen Asset Management LLC” was originally  published by Chaffey Breeze and is owned by of Chaffey Breeze. If you are accessing this news story on another publication, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of international trademark & copyright law. The correct version of this news story can be read at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/20/roper-technologies-inc-rop-position-lowered-by-nuveen-asset-management-llc.html. 
ROP has been the topic of several recent analyst reports. J P Morgan Chase & Co downgraded shares of Roper Technologies from an “overweight” rating to a “neutral” rating and set a $219.00 price target on the stock. in a research note on Friday, March 24th. Royal Bank Of Canada  reaffirmed a “buy” rating and issued a $245.00 price target on shares of Roper Technologies in a research note on Tuesday, April 11th. Zacks Investment Research downgraded shares of Roper Technologies from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Monday. Raymond James Financial, Inc. raised their price target on shares of Roper Technologies from $253.00 to $268.00 in a research note on Wednesday, July 5th. Finally, Cowen and Company  reaffirmed an “outperform” rating and issued a $250.00 price target (up previously from $220.00) on shares of Roper Technologies in a research note on Monday, April 17th. Three analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, eight have assigned  a buy rating and one  has assigned  a strong buy rating to the stock. The stock presently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and an average target price of $232.09.
In other Roper Technologies news, Director Christopher Wright sold 1,800 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction dated Friday, June 9th. The shares were sold at an average price of $228.70, for a total transaction of $411,660.00. Following the sale, the director now directly owns 66,104 shares in the company, valued at $15,117,984.80. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through the SEC website. 2.50% of the stock is owned by corporate insiders. 
