Company Overview of Sigma Investment Counselors, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Sigma Investment Counselors, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. The firm also provides wealth management services such as retirement planning, tax and estate planning, long-term care, life and disability insurance, charitable giving, and college funding strategies to its client. It provides its services to individuals, high net worth individuals, pension and profit sharing plans, charitable organizations, state or municipal government entities, estates, trusts, foundations, and endowments. The firm manages separate client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. The firm also invests in exchange traded f...
Sigma Investment Counselors, Inc. is an employee owned investment manager. The firm also provides wealth management services such as retirement planning, tax and estate planning, long-term care, life and disability insurance, charitable giving, and college funding strategies to its client. It provides its services to individuals, high net worth individuals, pension and profit sharing plans, charitable organizations, state or municipal government entities, estates, trusts, foundations, and endowments. The firm manages separate client-focused equity and fixed income portfolios. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. The firm also invests in exchange traded funds. For the fixed income portion, it invests in treasury bonds, notes or bills, certificates of deposit, municipal bonds, corporate bonds, and money market funds. The firm employs a combination of quantitative, qualitative, and fundamental analysis to create its portfolios. It conducts in-house research to make its investments. Sigma Investment Counselors, Inc. was founded in 1973 and is based in Southfield, Michigan with additional offices in Lake Mary, Florida and Pepper Pike, Ohio.
